Rule Learning, Probabilistic Methods. 

Rule Learning is the most related sub-category as the paper describes a machine learning method that induces solutions in the form of ordered disjunctive normal form (DNF) decision rules. The central objective of the method is to induce compact, easily interpretable solutions. 

Probabilistic Methods are also present as the paper mentions that the new techniques are competitive with existing machine learning and statistical methods and can sometimes yield superior regression performance. This suggests that the method involves some form of probabilistic modeling or inference.
